%description
Starlet is a standalone HTTP/1.0 server with keep-alive support, formerly known as the Plack::Server::Standalone::Prefork manpage and the Plack::Server::Standalone::Prefork::Server::Starter manpage.

The server supports following features, and is suitable for running HTTP application servers behind a reverse proxy.

- prefork and graceful shutdown using the Parallel::Prefork manpage

- hot deploy using the Server::Starter manpage

- fast HTTP processing using the HTTP::Parser::XS manpage (optional)

